==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-hearing.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*{{IPA|'hɪɹ.ɪŋ}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪərɪŋ|-ɪərɪŋ]]

===Adjective===
'''hearing'''
# Able to [[hear]].
#: ''Deaf people often must deal with '''hearing''' people.''

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''hearing''' (''plural:'' '''[[hearings]]''')
# The [[sense]] used to [[perceive]] [[sound]].
#: ''My '''hearing''' isn't what it used to be, but I still heard that noise.''
# A [[proceeding]] at which [[discussion]]s are [[heard]].
#: ''There will be a public '''hearing''' to discuss the new traffic light.''
# A legal procedure done before a judge, without a jury, as with an evidentiary hearing.

